This is a fairly up-to-date and highly readable introduction to the
Talmud, the age-old storehouse of Jewish wisdom. Bokser covers the long
history of the Talmud, from its origin in the Babylonian exile, its
growth through the five centuries after the Roman destruction of the
Temple, and the later persecution of the Talmud. The book covers a
number of high-level topics, including social ethics and personal
morality, with numerous examples from the Talmud. <span
class="small">--J.B. Hare, 1/3/2009.</span>

